@rjones and others, we would like to suggest renaming `aries-framework-rs` to `aries-vcx` - it's almost revert to the originally considered option `aries-vcx-rs`, but without the `rs`. 
The reason is that as the library isn't necessarily rust-only but contains wrappers for java, ios, nodejs (and unmaintaned python). So we realized putting Rust language reference is misleading, it also makes naming of wrapper packages awkward (for example having NodeJS wrapper `aries-framework-rs` is bit weird).
Removing the `rs` part from `aries-framework-rs` would make the name too general.

